HEADWORD: Hypothec
<hw>Hy*poth"ec</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>hypoth⟦egrave⟧que</ets>. See <er>Hypotheca</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Scot.
Law)</fld> <def>A landlord's right, independently of stipulation, over
the stocking (cattle, implements, etc.), and crops of his tenant, as
security for payment of rent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

